Never move branches. Never create a new branch. Never switch away from the current working branch. All work happens on the branch Alison is already on.

**Why:** Alison explicitly said "never ever move branches. NEVER EVER DO WORK ON ANOTHER BRANCH." Branch switching disrupts her workflow and state.

**How to apply:** Do not run `git checkout -b`, `git switch`, or `git checkout` to any other branch. Work on the current branch. If a branch strategy is needed, ask first — but default is: stay where you are.
